The paper deals with a graph theory problem of finding disjoint paths in a supply graph subject to constraints on a demand graph. This problem is a classic topic in discrete mathematics (cs.DM) and graph theory (cs.DS). The paper also discusses the complexity of the problem, which involves analyzing the structure of the demand graph, making it relevant to computational geometry (cs.CG) and theoretical computer science (cs.CC). Finally, the paper uses techniques from parameterized complexity, which is a subfield of algorithms and data structures (cs.DS).
